<TITLE> 4 die in Tangail truck-bus accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)  Four people were killed as a truck rammed into a bus on Wednesday at Mirzapur Bus Stand in Tangail. Two people died on the spot and 20 others were injured as the truck hit the back of a Dhaka-bound Jhatika Paribahan bus coming from Tangail, said Mirzapur police chief Jahangir Hossain. The accident, occuring at around 7.30am, propelled the bus into a roadside ditch, said the police chief. The dead were identified as 'Ganesh', 45, of Mirzapur Sadar Upazila, bus conductor Kagmarar Aslam, 27, of Sadar Upazila, Rostam Ali, 52, of Deuli village in Basail and 'Arjun', 45, of Kaliakir. The injured were admitted to Kumudini Hospital. Ganesh and Aslam died on the spot while the other two died in hospital. Injured bus passenger Abdur Rahim said the accident occured because of the carelessness of the truck driver. 
